    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/alexandria/paper/mercadier2011/run/e88f86e/element/21",
      "@type": "doco:Figure",
      "position": 21,
      "onPage": "https://w3id.org/alexandria/paper/mercadier2011/run/e88f86e/page/2",
      "figureType": "pax:micrograph",
      "description": "The figure shows two backscatter electron microscope (BSEM) images of zircon grains. The images illustrate zoning and alteration features within the zircons, with ages of different zones indicated.",
      "pax:parsedContent": "The image displays two separate scientific diagrams, labeled (A) and (B), each depicting a cross-sectional view of a geological formation. Both diagrams are in grayscale, with varying shades indicating different materials or geological features.\n\nIn diagram (A), the top portion of the image shows a detailed cross-section of a geological formation with various layers and structures. The layers are labeled with numbers 1 through 9, and the diagram includes annotations such as \"McArthur river,\" \"Unconformity-related,\" and \"Overgrowth.\" The core of the formation is marked with a number 1, and the alteration zone is indicated with a number 2. The diagram also includes a scale bar at the bottom, showing a measurement of 500 µm.\n\nDiagram (B) presents a similar cross-section but with a different set of annotations. The layers are labeled with numbers 1 through 9, and the diagram includes annotations such as \"Luthi Magmatic,\" \"Core,\" and \"Alteration band.\" The core is marked with a number 1, and the alteration band is indicated with a number 2. The scale bar at the bottom shows a measurement of 30 µm.\n\nBoth diagrams include a legend with the text \"Pb depleted, Ca-Si enriched,\" suggesting that the formation has undergone some form of metal enrichment. The diagrams are likely used to illustrate the geological processes and structures within the formation, such as the presence of different rock types and the extent of alteration or metal enrichment.",
      "region": [
